        "summary": "## Goal\n1. Maintain and improve the `ahv-openclaw-setup/` onboarding tool — credentials, skills, pipe mode, multi-team support\n2. Push a complete working setup package to `main` on `github.com/maiychrus25/setup-openclaw`\n3. **NEW (acknowledged misstep)**: Generate `team-dev.json` / `team-ba.json` / `team-qa.json` **based on the user's existing `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`** as a reference/template — not overwrite it; keep only **1 bot token**; each team has its own subset of agents; sensitive credentials (API keys, tokens) are user-supplied via env vars\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Do not infer or repeat old tasks from prior chats\n- Follow HEARTBEAT.md strictly — reply HEARTBEAT_OK if no material changes\n- **CRITICAL (new)**: Never modify `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` on the running system again — treat it as read-only reference only\n- Use exact workspace path `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/HEARTBEAT.md` for heartbeat context\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Fixed `bin/ahv-setup.js` — `applyCredentials`: init `config.env` and `config.models.providers.ahvholding` before setting properties (fixes \"Cannot set properties of undefined\")\n- [x] Rebuilt `skills.pack` from scratch (309 entries → 526 entries): 309 agent-defs files + 217 ecosystem skill reference files (SKILL.md, templates, references, scripts, data, evals)\n- [x] Fixed `bin/ahv-setup.js` unpack path: write to `path.join(destDir, \"skills\", entry.file)` → correct `~/.openclaw/skills/{agent}/...` for both agent-defs paths and ecosystem paths\n- [x] Fixed `install.sh`: use `SETUP_TEAM` env var instead of positional arg for pipe mode; added `--yes` auto-detection\n- [x] Added `buildAnswersFromEnv()` function: pipe/non-TTY mode reads credentials from `AHVHOLDING_API_KEY`, `GITLAB_TOKEN`, `CONF_URL`, `CONF_EMAIL`, `CONF_TOKEN`, `STITCH_API_KEY`, `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` env vars instead of prompting\n- [x] Added `--yes` skipIntro handling: skips team selection, confirmation prompt, write confirmation, and `restartGateway()` in pipe mode\n- [x] Added `team \"all\"` — all 34 agents + all 3 MCP servers (gitlab, confluence, stitch) + all credentials\n- [x] Removed project-specific agents from `agent-defs/`: `ahv-qlhv-fe`, `ahv-dtlx-backend`, `ahv-qlhv-be`, `ahv-openclaw-setup`, `setup-openclaw` — only 34 generic ecosystem agents remain\n- [x] Created `configs/team-all.json` — 34 agents, all MCP servers\n- [x] Pushed all changes to `feat/full-setup-mcp` → `main` (not `feat/complete-setup`)\n- [x] **INCIDENT**: `bin/ahv-setup.js` overwrote `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` — **RESTORED from backup** at `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-1776304957486.json` (timestamp `02:02:38 UTC`); the overwritten version saved as `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.restored-away-20260416T025256`\n- [x] Full piped install confirmed working end-to-end on the system\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **Generate team configs FROM existing `openclaw.json`**: read `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` as read-only baseline to understand the correct schema and structure; produce `configs/team-dev.json`, `configs/team-ba.json`, `configs/team-qa.json` as templates — each with its own agent subset and **1 shared bot token placeholder**; all sensitive values replaced with env var placeholders\n- [ ] **Fix installer to never overwrite existing `openclaw.json`**: change to write output as `~/.openclaw/openclaw.generated.json` or prompt before touching existing config\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **`skills.pack` encryption bug**: Original `encrypt()` XOR'd `data_bytes` (content) instead of `compressed` bytes → all decrypts failed. Fixed: `compressed = zlib.compress(data_bytes)` then XOR the compressed bytes. All 526 entries verified OK.\n- **`skills.pack` manifest path**: Original pack had `{agent}/skills/{agent}/SKILL.md` (extra `skills/` nesting) which caused unpack to write to `~/.openclaw/skills/skills/{agent}/SKILL.md`. Fixed manifest to `{agent}/SKILL.md` and unpack writes to `path.join(destDir, \"skills\", entry.file)`.\n- **Repo is private**: `raw.githubusercontent.com` returned 404 — solved by confirming the URL works (HTTP 200) despite private repo. SSH git operations work fine.\n- **\"all\" team default**: When `skipIntro=true` and no team specified, defaults to `team = \"dev\"` (not \"all\")\n- **Team configs template source**: `configs/team-*.json` templates were created from scratch with minimal structure (`name`, `description`, `agents`, `mcp`) — **NOT derived from the actual user's `openclaw.json`**. Lead clarified this was the wrong approach.\n- **`~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` is sacred**: The setup script's `applyConfig()` was writing directly to `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` unconditionally. This must never happen again — the running system's config must be treated as read-only reference.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Read `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`** (read-only) as baseline to understand the real schema used by this system\n2. **Generate `configs/team-dev.json`, `configs/team-ba.json`, `configs/team-qa.json`** from that schema:\n   - Each team: specific subset of agents (e.g. dev=backend/frontend/devops, ba=po/strategy/epic, qa=qa/playwright/security)\n   - 1 shared bot token placeholder (not per-team)\n   - All sensitive credentials → env var placeholders\n3. **Fix `applyConfig()`**: write to a new file name (e.g. `openclaw.generated.json`) or prompt before touching existing config\n4. **Commit and push** to `feat/full-setup-mcp` → `main`\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Setup repo**: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/` — standalone git repo at `git@github.com:maiychrus25/setup-openclaw.git`\n- **Current branch**: `feat/full-setup-mcp` (pushed to `main`)\n- **Last commit on main**: `b98efa6` — \"feat(setup): add 'all' team — all 34 agents + all MCP servers\"\n- **`skills.pack`**: 526 entries, 1.4 MB, key `ahv-openclaw-2026`, decrypt: `buf[i] ^ key[i % len(key)] ^ (i & 0xff)` → `zlib.inflateSync(dec)`\n- **Running system's `openclaw.json`**: RESTORED at `02:52 UTC` from backup; original config preserved at `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.restored-away-20260416T025256`\n- **HEARTBEAT state**: Pipeline HEALTHY. Night silence window (UTC+7 23:00–07:00 = UTC 16:00–00:00). Current UTC time of recent polls: 21:54–02:42 UTC. Status: HEARTBEAT_OK throughout.\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n\n## Original Request\nThe user asked to build a corrected `setup-openclaw` system for the AHV OpenClaw ecosystem, with separate team configs (dev, ba, qa, all) that:\n- Template out all credentials (env var placeholders like `${AHVHOLDING_API_KEY}`)\n- Keep only 1 bot token placeholder (not multiple hardcoded ones)\n- Never overwrite existing `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\n\n## Early Progress\n- Read the existing `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` to understand its full structure (top-level keys, models, channels, agents list, bindings, MCP servers)\n- Identified the key env vars to template: `AHVHOLDING_API_KEY`, `GITLAB_TOKEN`, `GITLAB_URL`, plus MCP-specific ones (Confluence, Stitch)\n- Identified the existing `bin/ahv-setup.js` had multiple bugs: it tried to filter by agent IDs in `team-*.json` (which contained full objects, not IDs), loaded a non-existent `openclaw-full.json`, and used wrong env var names\n- Generated clean team configs: `team-dev.json` (12 agents, MCP: gitlab/confluence/stitch), `team-ba.json` (7 agents, MCP: confluence/stitch), `team-qa.json` (6 agents, MCP: gitlab/confluence), `team-all.json` (34 agents, all MCP)\n- Discovered `openclaw-full.json` already existed with the full 34-agent structure\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe suffix begins with examining `ahv-setup.js` functions: `applyCredentials` (builds a `vars` map mapping answer field names → env values and applies them via `replacePlaceholders`), `installMcpServers`, and `collectCredentials`. The `applyCredentials` maps use specific env var names (`CONFLUENCE_URL`, `CONFLUENCE_EMAIL`) that need to match what the generated configs actually use (`CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL`, `CONFLUENCE_USERNAME`). The remaining work in the suffix likely addresses fixing these mismatches and verifying the full install flow.\n\n<modified-files>\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/bin/ahv-setup.js\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/install.sh\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/test-pipe.sh\n</modified-files>",
