        "summary": "## Goal\nBuild a complete **S1 PPE Safety Monitoring System** (AI Giám sát An toàn Lao động) for construction sites using Computer Vision (YOLO/OpenCV) + Flask backend + React dashboard. Goal was to demo detection of construction workers wearing safety helmets and vests in real-time.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- User insisted on using **spawned agents** rather than self-implementation (but `openclaw agents spawn` kept SIGKILL/timeouting)\n- MongoDB: user will provide their own URI (currently pointing to localhost:27017)\n- Camera source: **video file** (not webcam)\n- Output: `workspaces2/projects/`\n- Git: no push (temporary)\n- Dashboard must show **actual real video footage** with bounding boxes overlay (not just canvas simulation)\n- Video must load properly in browser (required Range request support)\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Project scaffolded at `workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/`\n- [x] Backend: `detector.py` (Edge+Blob+Color PPE detection, CPU-only, no external model downloads)\n- [x] Backend: `video_processor.py` (video file reader, frame processing loop)\n- [x] Backend: `app.py` (Flask + Socket.IO REST API: `/health`, `/api/detect`, `/api/summary`, `/api/alerts`, `/api/frame`, `/api/start`, `/api/stop`)\n- [x] MongoDB pymongo bool() bug fixed: `if alerts_collection:` → `if alerts_collection is not None:`\n- [x] Eventlet removed, threading mode used for Socket.IO\n- [x] Synthetic 15-second video generated via OpenCV (1280x720, 10fps, `demo.mp4`) showing 4 animated people with varying PPE compliance\n- [x] Frontend: React + Vite + Ant Design dashboard with HTML5 `<video>` element + canvas overlay for bounding boxes\n- [x] Video served from `frontend/public/video/demo.mp4` (Vite static, no Flask proxy)\n- [x] Both services verified running on VPS: Backend :5000, Frontend :3003\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] User still reporting \"Không thể tải video\" — last fix applied was moving video to Vite public dir and removing Flask proxy for `/video`\n\n### Blocked\n- Detection accuracy is limited: Edge+Blob+Color analysis is basic. Fine-tuned PPE YOLO model would be much better but couldn't be downloaded (disk space + network restrictions)\n- MongoDB currently uses localhost (user needs to provide their own URI)\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **ONNX YOLOv8 abandoned**: Couldn't install ultralytics (CUDA deps, 97% disk full), couldn't download ONNX model (URLs 404/401)\n- **Haar cascades abandoned**: Don't generalize well to arbitrary images\n- **Edge+Blob+Color chosen**: Works without ML models, uses OpenCV's built-in background subtraction + contour analysis\n- **Synthetic video generated**: Real Pexels/Pexels CDN videos blocked by Cloudflare; yt-dlp hit JS runtime issues\n- **Video served via Vite public**: Flask/Werkzeug dev server doesn't support Range requests for HTML5 video seeking; Vite's public dir serves properly\n- **Agents spawning failed**: `openclaw agents spawn` consistently hangs (SIGKILL), user frustrated → built directly\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Confirm with user that video now loads at **http://103.253.21.139:3003** after Ctrl+Shift+R refresh\n2. If still failing, check browser console for specific error (CORS, 404, etc.)\n3. User should provide MongoDB URI for alert persistence\n4. Consider upgrading to real YOLOv8 model when disk space available\n5. Replace synthetic video with real construction footage when user provides/uploaded\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Running PIDs**: Backend `python3 app.py` (check `pgrep`), Frontend `vite --port 3003`\n- **Backend logs**: `/tmp/s1-backend.log`\n- **Frontend logs**: `/tmp/s1-frontend.log`\n- **Synthetic video**: `backend/demo.mp4` + `frontend/public/video/demo.mp4` (688KB, 15s, 1280x720)\n- **Test image**: `/tmp/s1_scene.jpg`\n- **Detection pipeline**: `PPEDetector.detect_from_frame()` → Edge+Blob+Color → helmet (HSV yellow/orange) + vest (HSV orange/reflective) → compliance\n- **API_BASE in frontend**: empty (`''`) — video URL is `/video/demo.mp4`\n- **Vite proxy**: `/api` and `/socket.io` → localhost:5000; `/video` → served directly from `public/video/`\n- **Socket.IO**: `async_mode=\"threading\"`, callbacks: `on_violation_detected` (→ MongoDB + WS emit) and `on_detection_results` (→ WS emit summary)\n- **MongoDB**: `ppe_safety` database, `alerts` collection with indexes on `timestamp`, `camera_id`\n- **PPE detection on synthetic video**: ~4 people detected, 60-75% compliance rate, some false positives on background elements\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n\n## Original Request\nUser still cannot see video on the dashboard. They requested a split-screen layout: real video on top, annotated frame on bottom.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Identified `VideoPlayer` component in `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/src/App.jsx` (lines 64-277)\n- Video URL is `/video/demo.mp4`\n- Component uses `videoRef`, `canvasRef`, `detections`, `summary` state\n- Canvas drawing logic scales from 1280x720 to display size\n\n## Context for Suffix\nAssistant was about to rewrite the `VideoPlayer` function to implement:\n1. **Top panel**: Real HTML5 `<video>` element (1280x720)\n2. **Bottom panel**: Annotated frame image from backend `/api/frame` endpoint\n\nThis ensures the annotated frame displays regardless of video loading issues. The function boundaries are line 64 to line 277.\n\n<read-files>\n/root/.openclaw/agents/developer/SKILL.md\n/root/.openclaw/agents/senior-backend/SKILL.md\n/root/.openclaw/skills/prompt-optimizer/SKILL.md\nmemory/2026-04-21.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/README.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/.env.example\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/app.py\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/detector.py\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/requirements.txt\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/video_processor.py\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/devops/Dockerfile.backend\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/devops/docker-compose.yml\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/index.html\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/package.json\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/src/App.jsx\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/src/index.css\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/src/main.jsx\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/vite.config.js\n</modified-files>",
